content.raw: I think this is a left-over from when the `BuildingMaker` was derived from `gui::EntityMaker`. I think it's ok to make them private now.
content.html: I think this is a left-over from when the BuildingMaker was derived from gui::EntityMaker. I think it's ok to make them private now.

content.raw: Can't we remove any header from here?
content.html: Can't we remove any header from here?

content.raw: Were these two members intentionally created `protected`? If so we shouldn't include them in the private class.
content.html: Were these two members intentionally created protected? If so we shouldn't include them in the private class.

content.raw: How about if we convert this raw pointer to a `std::unique_ptr` and we remove the `delete` in the `BuildingMaker` destructor?
